<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1094" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1094">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.417/1103: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-06T14:00:00+09:00">December 6, 1940—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 6—9:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1281. Department’s 457, November 8, 4 p.m. In a formal note dated
                            December 2 the Foreign Office informs us that the Japanese Government
                            has given notice of abrogation of the Fur Seal Convention of 1911 to all
                            the signatories.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>